    <gsw_content_information action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <article><![CDATA[<p>Set the <em>x_taniu_tan_core.tanium_api_endpoint</em> system property to the URL or IP Address of your Tanium Server (including HTTPS) including the API path prefix (e.g. &#34;/api/v2&#34;).</p>
<p><strong>Example</strong>: https://192.168.7.193/api/v2</p>
<p><strong>Note</strong>: If using TaaS, the API url should have &#34;-api&#34; appended to the end of the first part of the subdomain. For example, if your instance URL is <em>https://taas-example.cloud.tanium.com</em> then the API endpoint for the core APIs (this property) should be set to <em>https://taas-example-api.cloud.tanium.com/api/v2</em>.</p>
<p> </p>]]></article>
